What you need to know:

The identified players will also benefit from a Zetech University scholarship programme worth Sh16 millionThe promising youth were selected during the recent inaugural Barasa Foundation Championship in Kakamega that attracted 1,234 teams from the 12 constituencies in the countyAmbani, who led other ex-internationals including Washington Muhanji, Fancis Xavier and Ramadhan Balala, to scout for talent, said they picked the best from a very talented pool